title: "My First Blog"
date: 2026-03-13
I am attempting to learn how to modify the Implicit Association Test for use in my research project. The directions are very friendly and clear, but in order to do it, so far, I've had to: 
1. Learn about The Center for Open Science and create an OSF account. https://osf.io/dashboard
2. Learn about DataPipe - a platform for sharing data from behavoral experiments to the OSF platform. I had to create an account, and then learn how to generate an OSF token and insert it into the code that was written for the Implicit Association Test so that it could link to the OSF platform. 
3. And last but certainly not least, I had to create a GitHub account in order to have somewhere to save the files of the test. Fortunately I already knew what GitHub was from another class, but I hadn't really understood how to use it. So...
4. I took an Introduction to GitHub lesson, which required some additional consultation with AI to get through. 
5. Finally, having completed the basics, I began a lesson on creating a website with GitHub (called GitHub Pages) - and that is where I am now. 
Welcome to my website!
